<subSubSection box="[189,966,1429,1456]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1429,2068]" box="[189,966,1429,1456]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,313,1429,1455]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">Phenology</emphasis>
:—Flowering in May and fruiting from July to November.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="202" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1429,2068]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,484,1465,1491]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
:—The species is known only from Napo, northwestern 
<collectingRegion box="[1115,1214,1465,1491]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1225,1296,1465,1491]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">China</collectingCountry>
. And it grows in wet but sunny limestone valleys. Only one small populations with 23 individuals (including only 19 mature trees) have been found in Napo. All mature trees are more than 
<quantity box="[772,828,1537,1564]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" unit="m" value="15.0">15 m</quantity>
in height and less than 
<quantity box="[1089,1132,1537,1564]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" unit="m" value="3.0">3 m</quantity>
is observed for all immature trees. The rarity of this new species may be partially due to human activity because the habitat is also suitable for cultivating cassava, tobacco and other economic plants. And the seeds are often aborted. Comparing to the number of mature trees, the number of immature trees further indicates a decreasing population trend. In addition, all these trees are distributed in a total area of approximately 
<quantity box="[728,807,1681,1707]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" unit="km" value="0.6">0.6 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[807,815,1681,1695]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">2</superScript>
. No population was found during repeated field surveys of the surrounding areas. According to the IUCN Categories and Criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[990,1130,1717,1743]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" refId="ref2828" refString="IUCN (2022) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria, Version 15. Available from: https: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 9 February 2022)" type="url" year="2022">IUCN 2022</bibRefCitation>
), the species is classified as Critically Endangered (CR: B1 + 2c). Therefore, it will be necessary to pay close attention to the conservation of this new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="202" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1429,2068]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,485,1825,1851]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">Taxonomic relationships</emphasis>
:—The comparison with the known species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1032,1132,1826,1851]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1032,1132,1826,1851]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">Reevesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
indicates that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Y. Feng Huang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1305,1451,1826,1851]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="napoensis">
<emphasis box="[1305,1451,1826,1851]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. napoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Chun (1934: 269" authorityName="Chun" authorityYear="1934" box="[279,648,1861,1887]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">
<emphasis box="[279,445,1861,1887]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. rotundifolia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chun, W. Y." box="[453,648,1861,1887]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" refId="ref2623" refString="Chun, W. Y. (1934) Flora of Kwangtung. Sunyatsenia 1: 269 - 230." type="journal volume" year="1934">Chun (1934: 269</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<figureCitation box="[661,728,1861,1888]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[136,229,2005,2027]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,190,1981]" captionTargetId="figure-29@6.[188,1399,190,1981]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Isotype of Reevesia rotundifolia. China, Guangxi, Shangsi (belong to Guangdong before), C. L. Tso 23605(IBSC0004177)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6534770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6534770/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tardieu" authorityYear="1945" box="[794,950,1861,1887]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orbicularis">
<emphasis box="[794,950,1861,1887]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. orbicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in sharing the characters of the orbicular or ovate-orbicular leaf blade but it has larger phenotypic divergence with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chun" authorityYear="1934" box="[930,1095,1897,1923]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">
<emphasis box="[930,1095,1897,1923]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. rotundifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tardieu" authorityYear="1945" box="[1149,1304,1897,1923]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orbicularis">
<emphasis box="[1149,1304,1897,1923]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. orbicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation box="[1319,1403,1897,1923]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="8.[136,224,159,183]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphological comparison between R. napoensis, R. rotundifolia and R. orbicularis." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/71D12496FFDEFFA9FF03FF553F92FF5A" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" tableUuid="71D12496FFDEFFA9FF03FF553F92FF5A">Table 1</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Y. Feng Huang" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="napoensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. napoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tardieu" authorityYear="1945" box="[399,555,1933,1959]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orbicularis">
<emphasis box="[399,555,1933,1959]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. orbicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the leaf blades upper margin with 3–5 teeth. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Y. Feng Huang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1107,1251,1934,1959]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="napoensis">
<emphasis box="[1107,1251,1934,1959]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. napoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chun" authorityYear="1934" box="[136,300,1969,1995]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">
<emphasis box="[136,300,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. rotundifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the leaf blades upper margin with teeth, but there are very obvious differences. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Y. Feng Huang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1229,1372,1970,1995]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="napoensis">
<emphasis box="[1229,1372,1970,1995]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. napoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tardieu" authorityYear="1945" box="[198,354,2005,2031]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orbicularis">
<emphasis box="[198,354,2005,2031]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. orbicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by cordate base, 7-veined base (vs. truncate or rounded 3-veined, bracts three (vs. one); calyx 4- lobed (vs. 3-lobed) and glabrous petals (vs. puberulent) (
<figureCitation box="[771,848,2041,2068]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1324,1346]" captionTargetBox="[236,1354,196,1289]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[222,1365,190,1300]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Reevesia napoensis (A-B) flowering branch, (C) top of inflorescence, (D) flower, (E) flowers, (F) flower, a. petal, b. calyx, c. bract. Photographs by Ms. Dong Xin Nong." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6534768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6534768/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">Figs. 5</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[884,900,2042,2068]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="7.[136,229,1581,1603]" captionTargetBox="[262,1326,190,1557]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[262,1326,190,1557]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 7. Reevesia rotundifolia (A–B) flowering branch, (C–D) flowers, (E) abaxial surface, (F) adaxial surface, (G) fruiting branch, (H) fruit. Photographs by Mr. Bing Liu." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6534772" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6534772/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
